HEADWORD: Poenamu
<hw>Po*e"na*mu</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A
variety of jade or nephrite, -- used in New Zealand for the manufacture
of axes and weapons.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

